Class DriveTrain

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.SendableBase
      • edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
        • frc.robot.subsystems.DriveTrain
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.Sendable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    public class DriveTrain
extends edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
    Drivetrain subsystem. Initilizes the 4 drivetrain talons based on robotconfig settings. Also, some motion profile stuff (which is hopefully depricated). Contains methods for setting PID values, shifting, getting drivetrain encoder status, setting speeds and voltages, and the arcade drive method.
